Here is a wonderful way to spend about an hour of your time, particularly if you are in anyway associated with software development. Listen to Grady Booch talks about &ldquo;The promise, the limits, the beauty of software&rdquo;. Apart from that he also talks about pimped out laptops, being half dead, and fun stuff like,
&ldquo;I looked at a machine from Siemens, and thought, Damn, I know the guys who wrote the software for this machine.&rdquo;
Apparently, they used UML to design that machine, that was used to scan him for his aneurysm. He talks about several such fun stuff and also about a lot of serious stuff about what&rsquo;s wonderful and also scary about software and the process of development.
Also, it is quite nice to see that the father of UML, is in with times (was it like 30 years ago he did that?!), and is in support of agile and iterative development methodologies.
&ldquo;We have build systems as an industry that are in the interstitial spaces of the world, and I believe that in the coming decade we will reach the point of no return.&rdquo;
A few more gems
&ldquo;Challenge for us as an industry is, how do we express the excitement, to the people that follow us,as to the beauty and elegance of the things we have done&rdquo;
A special mention of Cisco IOS:
&ldquo;The initial version was apparently about 30000 lines of code and was donated by the developer (employee #4 @ Cisco), and the current version is about 30-50 million lines of code. Some of the early elegance is disappearing and is a very very brittle system.&rdquo;
and of Britney Spears
&ldquo;Software creates new forms of artistic expression. They allow people like Britney Spears who have no musical talent, to make lots of money&rdquo;
Now who else can talk to you about Cisco IOS and Britney Spears in the same presentation! Also he plays Halo 3! Now go see it!
Technorati tags: Grady Booch, software system, beauty of software, video, software

I simply love that plugin - Batch categories, like a myriad of other wordpress users. (A thousand thanks to Stephanie Booth wouldn&rsquo;t suffice ;) ), but I had problems getting it to work in 1.5.1
Lots of results out there, that explain how to fix it, but none that lets a newbie get it up quickly. I know this is a repetition, but it still took my more than a day to get it fixed (mebbe it&rsquo;s my dull head.. but then again)
If you are brand new to Word press, here it. As simple as it gets (or atleast I think so&hellip; do get back in case you have doubts)
1. Download and install Batch-categories (0.9) from here.
2. Installing implies, that you copy the batch-categories.php file to /wp-admin/
3. Edit /wp-admin/batch-categories.php and do the modifications as detailed below
**Change this:
**
$title = __(&lsquo;Batch Categories&rsquo;);
$parent_file = &rsquo;edit.php&rsquo;;
require_once(&lsquo;admin-header.php&rsquo;);
to this:
$title = __(&lsquo;Batch Categories&rsquo;);
$parent_file = &rsquo;edit.php&rsquo;;
**require_once(&lsquo;admin.php&rsquo;);
**require_once(&lsquo;admin-header.php&rsquo;);
Save batch-categories.php. Now launching it in your browser directly, will give you the required functionality (batch editing categories ie )
4. If you want to include it as part of your admin screen, then open ****/wp-admin/menu.php
**Below this:
**
$submenu[&rsquo;edit.php&rsquo;][30] = array(__(&lsquo;Files&rsquo;), 8, &rsquo;templates.php&rsquo;);
**Add this:
**
$submenu[&rsquo;edit.php&rsquo;][40] = array(__(&lsquo;Batch Categories&rsquo;), 1, &lsquo;batch-categories.php&rsquo;);
**5. Edit /wp-admin/batch-categories.php and delete the following:
**
&lt; ul id=&ldquo;adminmenu2?&gt;
&lt; li&gt;&lt; a href=&ldquo;edit.php&rdquo;&gt;&lt; /a&gt;&lt; /li&gt;
&lt; li&gt;&lt; a href=&ldquo;edit-comments.php&rdquo;&gt;&lt; ?php _e(&lsquo;Comments&rsquo;) ?&gt;&lt; /a&gt;&lt; /li&gt;
&lt; li&gt;&lt; a href=&ldquo;moderation.php&rdquo;&gt;&lt; ?php _e(&lsquo;Awaiting Moderation&rsquo;) ?&gt;&lt; /a&gt;&lt; /li&gt;
&lt; li class=&ldquo;last&rdquo;&gt;&lt; a href=&ldquo;batch-categories.php&rdquo; class=&ldquo;current&rdquo;&gt;&lt; ?php _e(&lsquo;Batch Categories&rsquo;) ?&gt;&lt; /a&gt;&lt; /li&gt;
&lt; /ul&gt;
Well, I always beleive that if you want to learn, then you need to do things the hardest way possible. Then, the next time around you can eliminate that way and go on to more efficient ways. On that note, if you don&rsquo;t want to do all the editing yourself. You can find the files here. Just download them and put them in you wp-admin directory, and enjoy! Ofcourse, you better take all the backups required and don&rsquo;t spam me if something is screwed up in your database.
batch-categories.php menu.php Note: 1. Do not use left-click on the above link. Use right-click and &ldquo;Save Link As..&rdquo;/&ldquo;Save Target As..&rdquo; and rename the file to *.php instead of *.php.txt
2. The above files are valid for 1.5.1 Wordpress only. Please follow the manual procedure for later versions
Wishlist for batch categories(BC)
Since we are discussing BC here, I thought I&rsquo;ll jot down a couple things that would make BC really kewl
Display categories already assigned Instead of a combo, use a multiple listbox report category names instead of IDs UI for options like number of posts,etc Paging - displays all posts, but on different pages. Maybe I should get in touch with steph about this, but then before that I need start exploring php (I&rsquo;m a total novice on that)
